    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class and additional loading conditions are not required for 510(k) submission. All three QoIs pass pre-established acceptance bounds. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
